Commentary: This is a skier. Both had ample time but neither called for the catch. Wicketkeeper Walton rams into the chest of his captain Brathwaite, who is thrown back by the impact. Man down now .Brathwaite, though, hung onto the overhead catch despite that nasty collision. Brathwaite is down. Banged in short and outside off, Hafeez is late onto the pull and top-edges it hiiiiigh into the sky. Drops down into the hands of Brathwaite. Walton gets an earful from an angry captain
